Sentencas: A film percolation model is proposed for composite electrodes of solid oxide fuel cells (SOFCs).
Titulo: Film percolation for composite electrodes of solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The model is developed to predict the percolation properties of 2D-infinite structures which represent the structural characteristics of composite electrodes of electrochemical devices such as SOFCs.
Titulo: Film percolation for composite electrodes of solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The model can be used to estimate electrode properties, such as percolation probability, active three-phase boundary length and interfacial polarization resistance.
Titulo: Film percolation for composite electrodes of solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Compared with the classic percolation theory, which is particularly applicable to 3D-infinite bulks, the model can explicitly capture the effects of thinly layered nature of composite electrodes, and describes a cross-over between 2D-infinite films and 3D-infinite bulks.
Titulo: Film percolation for composite electrodes of solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: It also permits the prediction within whole electrode composition range, and can be easily applied in SOFC modeling.
Titulo: Film percolation for composite electrodes of solid oxide fuel cells
